-- Ukio Shares Rise Most in 2 Years as Capital Increase Is Approved
-- B y   M i l d a   S e p u t y t e
-- 2011-12-22T10:15:51Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-12-22/ukio-shares-rise-most-in-2-years-as-capital-increase-is-approved.html
Shares of  Ukio Bankas AB (UKB1L) ,
Lithuania’s sixth-biggest bank by assets, surged the most in
more than two years after the central bank approved the bank’s
capital increase.  Ukio rose as much as 10.5 percent to 0.179 euro ($0.24),
the biggest one-day increase since Sept. 15, 2009. The shares
traded up 9.3 percent at 0.177 euro at 11:58 a.m. in Vilnius.
Ukio had fallen 54 percent this year.  Lietuvos Bankas  approved Ukio to raise its capital by 17
percent, or 50 million litai ($18.96 million), to 345.8 million
litai, the Vilnius-based central bank said in a statement today.
Ukio sold 50 million litai in new shares from June through
August.  To contact the reporter on this story:
